<Category category="Oil Temperature Indicators" slug="transformer-oil-temperature-indicators" title="Transformer Oil Temperature Indicator Manufacturer | INNO" description="Compare BWY and BWY2 transformer oil temperature indicators (OTI) for top-oil measurement, cooling contacts and remote output. Request a quotation." heading="Transformer Oil Temperature Indicators (OTI)" eyebrow="BWY and BWY2 manufacturer and supplier" intro="Select an OTI for local transformer top-oil indication, cooling control, high-temperature alarm and compatible remote measurement." definition="A transformer oil temperature indicator, or OTI, senses oil temperature at a thermometer pocket in the upper oil region. BWY and BWY2 models provide local indication and can operate contacts for transformer cooling or alarm functions." selectionTitle="How to Select a Transformer Oil Temperature Indicator" selectionText="Start with the required top-oil scale and the thermometer pocket. Then define the number and purpose of cooling or alarm contacts, Pt100 or 4-20 mA output, capillary route, bulb dimensions, M27 × 2 thread and outdoor installation conditions." />
